  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount embezzled ($25,000) and the defendant's lack of prior criminal history. Considering standard sentencing guidelines for non-violent white-collar crime of this magnitude, an 8-month period of incarceration is a sufficient punitive and rehabilitative measure.",
  "verdict": 8
